  "examples": [
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I want to synchronize new user registration information to the CRM via webhook, and retry and alert when API calls fail. Can you help me design an n8n workflow?"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yes. First confirm a few points: 1) Which system does the webhook come from (format example); 2) What is the CRM's authentication method (API Key/OAuth); 3) What is the failure retry strategy (immediate retry/delayed multiple retries); 4) Do you need to log or persist failures? I will first provide a high-level flow and key nodes, then produce an importable n8n JSON based on the details you confirm."
    },
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "The webhook comes from our in-house service and sends JSON. The CRM uses a Bearer Token. On failure, we want to retry every 5 minutes up to 3 times; after failures send a Slack alert and retain failure records."
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Understood. Recommended flow: [Webhook Trigger] → [Set (data cleaning)] → [HTTP Request (call CRM, Bearer Token)] → [IF (200?/condition check)] → on success proceed to follow-up (record/notify) → on failure go to retry flow (Wait 5 min → HTTP Request, counting) → if retry count exceeded, write to failure table and trigger Slack notification. If needed, I can generate the complete n8n JSON, sample Function expressions, and credential configuration instructions."
    }
  ],
